What is the equation of the following graph in terms of the sine function?

generalfeedback.text: Recall that the general sine function is written as \(y = a \sin b(x-c)+d\). First notice that the graph is of a wave form which oscillates between \(-1\) and \(3\). Therefore the amplitude is \((3 + 1)/2 = 2\), hence \(a = 2\). Now notice that the principal axis is the line \(y = 1\) so \(d =1\). Finally, looking at the positive part of the graph we can see that there are three periods from \(0^\circ\) to \(360^\circ\) rather than one. i.e. the period is \(360^\circ /120^\circ = 3\), hence \(b =3\). Hence the equation of the graph is \[ y={@ta1@} \]
